The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 Exit shut for kings aide

 J. HEMANTH 

 Kathmandu, May 13: The Nepal government today prevented King Gyanendras close aide and former army chief General Pyar Jung Thapa from leaving the country. 

 Thapa was stopped by immigration authorities at the Tribhuvan International Airport as he was boarding a Qatar Airways flight to Doha on his way to London.

 Police said he was stopped on the direction of the home ministry and the Commission for Investigation of Abuse of Authority. 

 The order was issued against those indicted for their alleged role in suppressing last Aprils pro-democracy movement. Thapa was one of them.




